# Procfile is a command to the heroku instance, that is when our application started what commands needs to run, the commands to use is related to the unicorn, that is the green unicorn, which is the purest python  http server for wsgi applications, It allows you to run Python applications concurrently by running multiple process

# g unicorn allows the entire python application run in an amazing way because ,it creates multiple Python processes, therefore based on the number of requests whenever the client is putting up supposed thousands of users are hitting this particular website or web applications, it make sure that it distributes the entire request through multiple instances and many more things.

web: gunicorn app:app
# the first app is the file name "app.py" and the second app is the "the application name"
